    "body": "## Summary\n- add end-to-end `T.int4` support for the `T.gemm` frontend path and switch the int4 GEMM tests to the generic tensor core emitters\n- lower eligible global-to-shared async copies directly to their final packed `cp.async` width during async copy injection instead of relying on a later vectorization pass to widen them\n- add an int4 GEMM example and a frontend compilation test, and remove the stale dead `CPAsyncStoreRewriter` path\n\n## Details\n- `TensorCoreIntrinEmitter` / `TensorCoreIntrinEmitterWithLadderTransform` can now infer the sub-byte MMA path from the input dtype, so the int4 tests no longer depend on the dedicated INT4 emitter classes\n- `InjectPTXAsyncCopy` now computes packed transfer width in bits, requires exact byte alignment, and folds vectorized copy loops directly into a single final-width `ptx_cp_async` when the transfer is legal\n- the late vectorization passes no longer try to widen already-materialized `cp.async` ops\n- added `examples/gemm_int4/example_tilelang_gemm_int4.py` and `testing/python/kernel/test_tilelang_kernel_int4_gemm.py` to cover the new frontend path\n\n## Validation\n- `bash format.sh --files src/op/copy.cc src/transform/loop_vectorize.cc src/transform/lower_ptx_async_copy.cc src/transform/vectorize_loop.cc tilelang/engine/phase.py tilelang/intrinsics/mma_macro_generator.py tilelang/language/dtypes.py tilelang/tileop/gemm/gemm_mma.py tilelang/utils/tensor.py testing/python/kernel/test_tilelang_kernel_int4_gemm_mma.py testing/python/kernel/test_tilelang_kernel_int4_gemm.py examples/gemm_int4/example_tilelang_gemm_int4.py`\n- `python examples/gemm_int4/example_tilelang_gemm_int4.py`\n- `pytest -q testing/python/kernel/test_tilelang_kernel_int4_gemm.py`\n- `pytest -q testing/python/kernel/test_tilelang_kernel_int4_gemm_mma.py`\n\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added an int4 GEMM TileLang example and a CUDA compile test for int4 kernels.\n\n* **Improvements**\n  * cp.async semantics now use logical element counts (num_elems) with validated byte sizing, improving vectorized cp.async handling and multi-backend codegen.\n  * Dtype mapping updated to better handle int4 for PyTorch/storage.\n\n* **Refactor**\n  * Unified tensor-core MMA emission to support sub-byte (int4) operands; removed legacy async-store rewrite and stray debug prints.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
